description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an apprentice to join the Property Team within the Estates &amp; Facilities Directorate at Nottingham University Hospitals NHS Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be eager to learn and have the ability to study to achieve a Level 2 in Customer Service as well as functional skills in English, Maths and ICT.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will have good communication skills, be willing to learn and have an enthusiasm for learning to develop on a variety of tasks covering areas such as Sustainability (waste, energy, travel) Information (surveys and records) and Workforce Systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be self-motivated and familiar with Microsoft packages and be confident to use various information management systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will receive a full induction and introduction to the Trust meaning you will be guided through from the start of your Apprenticeship, learning at work and enhancing your skills and confidence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lorraine Horsley - Planning &amp; Workforce Systems Officer&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;lorraine.horsley@nuh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Glenn Price (glenn.price@nuh.nhs.uk)&lt;/p&gt;
